cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.MA, cs.DS

This paper deals with the analysis of information freshness in a network with multiple servers and sources, which involves topics related to networked systems, information theory, control systems, and data science. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also involves stochastic modeling and analysis of queueing systems, which falls under cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.SY (Systems and Control). Additionally, the paper uses mathematical tools such as probability theory and optimization, which are relevant to cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
